  "why": "ASDF applies text-level mutations (e.g., tense changes, homophone substitution) that are designed to preserve plausibility at each transformation step and it explicitly filters out transformed inputs that are unrealistic by requiring at least one ASR to correctly transcribe them. However, the paper does not describe any mechanism that explicitly controls or measures cumulative distortion across multiple rounds of mutation (e.g., bounding perturbation relative to the original seed or restricting search to a learned plausible distribution). The workflow uses only a two-iteration pipeline (original then transformed texts) and relies on per-step validity checks rather than explicit cumulative-distortion control, matching the metric's 'Medium' definition.",
